1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the modeling of sequential data in social networks and information cascades, which falls under the scope of cs.SI.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper discusses the development of a framework for modeling sequential data, which can be relevant to software engineering.
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a model selection technique for inferring the optimal number of layers in a multi-layer graphical model, which is a machine learning problem.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the modeling of pathways in transportation systems and biological pathways, which can be relevant to systems and control.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the development of new data mining and knowledge discovery algorithms, which falls under the scope of cs.DS.
